id: pm-t5ud
title: Design full pm package manifest and resource model
description: Define the general pm package manifest contract without agent-specific resources. Package roots can declare pm.extensions only; direct Pi agent integration and prompt/skill/MCP resource semantics stay out of the main pm CLI/SDK.
type: Task
status: closed
priority: 0
tags[5]: manifest,packages,planning,pm-cli,sdk
created_at: "2026-05-11T17:58:43.930Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-17T08:22:44.272Z"
author: codex-agent
acceptance_criteria: Package manifest schema is documented and represented in SDK/contracts; resource precedence is explicit for runtime extensions; direct Pi agent code and package metadata are removed from the main codebase; focused package/SDK/install tests pass.
parent: pm-59gj
resolution: Metadata-first package resource contract was delivered with extension-only activation semantics and no direct agent-specific resource model in core.
expected_result: "Package manifest schema is documented, SDK-visible, and keeps direct Pi resource semantics out of pm core."
actual_result: "Package manifest, SDK, extension, dogfood, coverage, release gate, and plugin smoke verification passed."
comments[4]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-11T17:58:43.930Z",codex-agent,"Plan item created from Pi research: Pi packages bundle extensions,skills,prompts,and themes through package.json resource arrays and conventional directories. pm first slice supports extension resources; broader resource kinds need an explicit manifest design."
  "2026-05-11T20:05:29.769Z",codex-agent,"Implementation update: package manifest contract now exposes only pm.extensions for general project-management extension packages. Removed direct Pi runtime/package assets from the main codebase, renamed provider-safe SDK schema exports to provider-neutral names, removed Pi package metadata and optional peer dependency from package.json, and changed the todos extension default folder from .pi/todos to .pm/todos."
  "2026-05-14T15:37:48.330Z",codex-package-refactor,"Implemented metadata-first package resource expansion: core manifest contract now supports extensions/docs/examples, package install/catalog surfaces communicate extension-only activation semantics, and first-party package manifests now publish docs/examples metadata resources. Focused tests updated and passing."
  "2026-05-14T15:49:52.921Z",codex-package-refactor,"Verification complete: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/package-manifest.spec.ts tests/unit/sdk-index.spec.ts tests/unit/extension-command.spec.ts passed (60 tests); node scripts/dogfood-package-first.mjs passed; node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage passed (1299/1299, 100%); node scripts/release/run-gates.mjs --telemetry-mode required --max-sentry-critical 10 --max-sentry-high 20 --max-telemetry-error-rate 10 --json passed with sentry critical=1 high=4 and telemetry finish_error_rate_pct=2.24; node scripts/smoke-claude-plugin.mjs passed."
